# @jx3/jx3api Conventions

## Purpose

`@jx3/jx3api` wraps external JX3 game data APIs behind typed, testable methods.
Apps (`api`, `web` server functions) import from here — never call upstream URLs directly.

## Layout

```
packages/jx3api/src/
  client.ts       — shared fetchJson helper
  errors.ts       — Jx3ApiError
  index.ts        — public barrel exports
  providers/
    <provider>/   — one folder per upstream (e.g. jx3box)
      config.ts   — base URLs, constants
      types/      — raw API types + normalized domain types + mappers
      <endpoint>.ts — one exported function per upstream endpoint
```

## Adding an endpoint

1. Add raw + normalized types under `providers/<provider>/types/`.
2. Map snake_case upstream fields to camelCase domain types in a `map*` function.
3. Implement the method in `providers/<provider>/<endpoint>.ts` using `fetchJson`.
4. Re-export from `providers/<provider>/index.ts` and `src/index.ts`.
5. Add tests under `tests/providers/<provider>/` with mocked `fetch`.

## HTTP & errors

- Use `fetchJson` from `client.ts` for all outbound requests.
- Throw `Jx3ApiError` with a stable `code` (`NETWORK_ERROR`, `HTTP_ERROR`, `PARSE_ERROR`).
- Accept optional `logger` from `@jx3/logger` in public methods; do not `console.log`.

## Exports

- Default entry `@jx3/jx3api` — stable public API for apps.
- Subpath `@jx3/jx3api/<provider>` — provider-scoped imports when needed.
